# Morning_beauty — Project Standards

## General

- Minimum iOS version: **17.0**
- App is **portrait-only by design**, but all orientations are enabled in project settings
- Always use `screenHeight` from `SizeExtension` for vertical sizing instead of hardcoded values or `UIScreen`
- No comments anywhere in source files
- Follow Apple **Human Interface Guidelines (HIG)** at all times

## Architecture — MVVM

- Strictly follow MVVM: Model, ViewModel, View layers separated
- ViewModels: `@Observable` (iOS 17) or `ObservableObject`
- Views contain no business logic — only presentation and user interaction

## File & Folder Structure

```
Morning_beauty/
  Views/          ← all SwiftUI views, one file per view
  ViewModels/     ← one ViewModel per feature
  Models/         ← data models
  Extensions/     ← helpers and extensions (SizeExtension lives here)
```

## Views

- Each view in its own dedicated file inside `Views/`
- Every view file must include a `#Preview` block at the bottom
- Break complex views into smaller subviews in separate files

## Text Fields & Placeholders

- Placeholder text must look identical in both light and dark mode
- Use explicit color for placeholders — never rely on system default:

```swift
TextField("Placeholder", text: $text)
    .foregroundStyle(.primary)
    .overlay(alignment: .leading) {
        if text.isEmpty {
            Text("Placeholder")
                .foregroundStyle(Color(.placeholderText))
                .allowsHitTesting(false)
        }
    }
```

Or apply a consistent tint/foreground to `prompt` label explicitly.

## SizeExtension Usage

```swift
// ✅ Preferred
height: screenHeight * 0.12

// ❌ Avoid
height: UIScreen.main.bounds.height * 0.12
height: 90
```
